titles: All Things New | DAZED AND CONFUSED

texts.html: August 19, 2014August 20, 2014 / emsnyder95

It’s been a little while since I’ve posted, so my apologies. I have been SO busy! I just got a new job so that has definitely been taking up a lot of my time and the Fall Semester starts this coming Tuesday. It’s been crazy, but it’s been so good. I’ve found that I am at my happiest and best when I have a lot of things to do. It’s not good for me to be isolated for very long and this past week has been really wonderful. The distraction keeps me from thinking about people, my past and regrets and that is what’s best for me right now.

I’ve found that I am at my happiest and best when I have a lot of things to do. It’s not good for me to be isolated for very long and this past week has been really wonderful. The distraction keeps me from thinking about people, my past and regrets and that is what’s best for me right now.

texts.html: This is a new chapter starting for me. It’s hard letting go of the past and some days are still horrible, but I’m learning. I’m making new relationships, beginning a new semester and starting a new job. The people at my work are so cool and I’m absolutely excited to get to know them better. Over the past few months I’ve really lost a lot of my friends. And it’s understandable because I really messed up with them. But I also realized the ones who were really there for me, regardless of my screwed up actions. And I also realized the ones who were NEVER there for me even when I thought they were. So, maybe in the long run I’ve been better off for it. But regardless, I’ve said a lot of goodbyes and they were all hard and painful. It never becomes easier and you never really forget them.

texts.html: Anyway, this is where I am. The past few months I have been constantly thinking “good things are coming, good things are coming, good things are coming…” And those good things have finally gotten here and I couldnt be more excited. I don’t know how long they’re staying but I’m holding onto them for as long as possible.
text: Anyway, this is where I am. The past few months I have been constantly thinking
“good things are coming, good things are coming, good things are coming…”
And those good things have finally gotten here and I couldnt be more excited. I don’t know how long they’re staying but I’m holding onto them for as long as possible.

texts.html: To all of you wonderful humans, remember that there are dark days. Days that everything seems done. That you’ve ruined every single aspect of your life and hurt everyone you’ve ever cared about. But there are brighter days. And they are coming. They may not be here yet and they might not stay long. But remember that they do exist and that pain, sadness, grief, longing and regret is all temporary. Good things are coming!
